## Lagged by Prior Observed Value

Since the general idea is that prior values of aggregated external efficacy account for a portion of subsequent values of the same, then it seems reasonable enough to simply regress external efficacy on the most recent observed values of itself instead of its value four years prior.

I run the same analysis lagging the dependent variable by it's preceding value, i.e., the average index value of the previous ANES survey iteration. Moreover, I lag the trust-in-government index by its prior value as well for the models that include the aggregated index.


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code .hidden}
