# LDV model is unwarrented

It is not necessary to lag the dependent variable, and there's good reason not to; a lagged dependent variable is apt to soak up all influence from the predictors, especially if serial autocorrelation is present. Chamberlain doesn't provide a check for serial autocorrelation.

However, it is not necessary even theoretically. Even taking Chamberlain's contention that respondent's take past government performance and economic conditions into consideration, there's no good reason to then lag the dependent variable as well. Given the logic provided, we might as well include lagged variables for every attitudinal outcome of interest consistently measured in national election studies. 
